<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-09T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-09T20:00:00-05:00" n="431" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d431">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 865.857/26</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJC1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d431fn1">The same to the Ambassador in Austria-Hungary,
                                    No. 1446.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-09T20:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 9, 1916, 8 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3655. Department advised that Italian <persName>S. S. <hi rend="italic">Palermo, en route</hi>
                                </persName> from New York to Genoa with cargo of horses, was
                                torpedoed without warning by submarine of unknown nationality 25
                                miles off Cape San Sebastian, Spain, December 2, 11.40 a. m.; that
                                no attempt was made to escape or resist, and that there were on
                                board 48 Americans, of whom one was drowned.</p>
                            <p>Please bring this case to attention of Foreign Minister, with urgent
                                request for prompt investigation and report on sinking of this
                                vessel.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>